3.1

Implementation aspects
Interpolation

Since (XÌ‚, YÌ‚ ) is obtained by backtracking, then this point is not necessarily the node of a grid
block at time level n. As all the functions are defined only on the grid nodes, then an interpolation technique is necessary for the effective computation of the h1 (xÌ‚(t), yÌ‚(t)) and h2 (xÌ‚(t), yÌ‚(t)).
A simplified version of the inverse distance weighted interpolation formula developed by [4] was
tested by [8] in the context of a formulation of the Path Tubes method for advection equations.
In this work, the inverse distance weighted interpolation formula is employed. Let h be a function defined only on the grid nodes. Given (xr , ys ) âˆˆ â„¦r,s at time t + âˆ†t, we want to calculate
